";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"WPTavern: How To Search For 100% GPL Themes On Themeforest";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=6831";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:109:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/iD6061j0jLA/how-to-search-for-100-gpl-themes-on-themeforest";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2267:"<p>Not long ago, <a href="http://notes.envato.com/general/100-gpl-option-now-available-plus-woothemes-arrives/">Themeforest announced</a> that theme authors would be able to choose a 100% GPL theme license. However, as a customer, it&#8217;s difficult to find where those 100% GPL licensed themes are located on the site. Upon browsing the Themeforest Marketplace, I could not find a <em>category, tag, or link</em> that would show me all the WordPress themes licensed as such. Since the text located within the license information box is able to be crawled by Google, you can use a Site specific search query to find these themes. Just type <em>site:http://themeforest.net/item This item is licensed 100% GPL.</em> into Google to see a list of themes that have been indexed. </p>
<p><a href="http://i1.wp.com/www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/themeforestGPL.jpg" rel="thumbnail"><img src="http://i1.wp.com/www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/themeforestGPL.jpg?resize=532%2C265" alt="ThemeForest GPL Search String" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6838" /></a></p>
<p>While I saw 53,800 results listed, not all the results take you directly to the theme page. For example, the License text is also shown on the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/hustle/discussion/4137914">discussion pages</a> for each theme which is also indexed. Until Themeforest creates a better way of browsing these specific themes, this will have to do. </p>
<p><strong>Hat Tip:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/bradleypotter/statuses/331854378078203904">@Bradleypotter</a></p>
